This is the front for the numbers-map CTF challenge.

ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
PORT #PORT if you want to change it, default is 80
BACKEND_URL #BACKEND_URL for calls to backend. For example http://bqckend-test-ctf.h7fybef5f6cyc2hb.eastus.azurecontainer.io

LOCAL RUN
In order to run the project locally, run npm install and then npm start.

DOCKER IMAGE CREATION
In order to create a new docker image and push it, run : docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 -t sbutruil/ctf-numberschallenge-frontend:0.0.3  --push  .

CURRENT DOCKER IMAGES
You can find the image to this challenge on docker : https://hub.docker.com/r/sbutruil/ctf-numberschallenge-frontend
The latest usable image is : docker pull sbutruil/ctf-numberschallenge-frontend:0.0.3
